lead_paragraph: Rejecting pleas for leniency and a new trial, a judge Friday sentenced 24-year-old Jeen Han to 26 years to life in prison for conspiring to kill her twin sister. The woman, convicted in November with two teen-agers, told the judge that she never had any intention of killing her sister, Sunny Han. ''I'm deeply sorry for everything that has happened,'' she said.
abstract: Judge sentences Jan Han to 26 years to life in prison for conspiring to kill her twin sister Sunny Han, Santa Ana, Calif (S)

headline.main: National News Briefs; Woman Jailed 26 Years For Trying to Kill Twin
